NT|^B@2
However, I do not like that approach, because now your club and diamond distribution is very ambiguous (you could have 4 diamonds, 5 diamonds, 4 clubs, or 5 clubs). Playing weak NT, if the auction proceeds 1@D-1@H/@S-2@C, you are guaranteeing 5 diamonds and 4+ clubs. Granted, if you open this hand 1@C, you may have to rebid an anemic 5 card club suit, but your partner understands this is part of the system. 
|hc|sahkdacq|
