Bid 2@C. If partner responds 2@S, I would bid 4@S but 3@S is acceptable if conservative. If partner responds 2@D, bid 2N. If partner bids 2@H, bid 2@S. This shows an invitational hand with 4 spades. Playing 4 suit transfers, starting with 2@C does not guarantee a 4-card major. So by bidding 2@S over 2@H, you are saying you do have an invitational hand with 4 spades. If partner is 4-4 in the majors he will be able to place the contract in spades
